HEADWORD: Sea marge
<hw>Sea" marge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>Land which borders on the sea;
the seashore.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are near the <qex>sea marge</qex> of a land teeming with
life.</q> <rj><qau>J. Burroughs.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seamark</ent>⟦br⟧
